<body bgcolor='#FFFFFF' onload="javascript:{if(parent.frames[0]&&parent.frames['navig'].Go)parent.frames['navig'].Go()}">
<p align="left">Below are installation instructions for inserting HVMenu in a
frames page, where the main menu resides in one frame, and the resulting
submenus drop down in another. For an example, see: <a href="http://www.burmees.nl/">http://www.burmees.nl/</a>
<center>
<div align="left">
<table>
	<tr><td><h1>Step 1: Create frameset</h1></td>
	<td width='50'></td>
	<td>
      </td></tr>
</table>
</div>
</center>
<p align="left">
<span class='bigred'>Create frameset with coloms</span>
<table>
	<tr><td width='30'></td>
	<td>&lt;html&gt;<br>&lt;head&gt;<br>&lt;title&gt;Your Title&lt;/title&gt;<br>&lt;/head&gt;<br>
		&lt;frameset <span class='redtxt'>cols</span>="<span class='bluetxt'>150</span>,*" framespacing='0' frameborder='0' border=0&gt;<br>
		&lt;frame frameborder='0' framespacing='0' src="<span class='bluetxt'>MyNavigation.htm</span>" noresize scrolling='no' name="<span class='bluetxt'>MyFrameOne</span>"&gt;&lt;/frame&gt;<br>
		&lt;frame frameborder='0' framespacing='0' src="<span class='bluetxt'>MyMain.htm</span>" name="<span class='bluetxt'>MyFrameTwo</span>"&gt;&lt;/frame&gt;<br>
		&lt;/frameset&gt;<br>&lt;/html&gt;</td></tr></table>
<p align="left">
<span class='bigred'>Create frameset with rows</span>
<table>
	<tr><td width='30'></td>
	<td>&lt;html&gt;<br>&lt;head&gt;<br>&lt;title&gt;Your Title&lt;/title&gt;<br>&lt;/head&gt;<br>
		&lt;frameset <span class='redtxt'>rows</span>="<span class='bluetxt'>150</span>,*" framespacing='0' frameborder='0' border=0&gt;<br>
		&lt;frame frameborder='0' framespacing='0' src="<span class='bluetxt'>MyNavigation.htm</span>" noresize scrolling='no' name="<span class='bluetxt'>MyFrameOne</span>"&gt;&lt;/frame&gt;<br>
		&lt;frame frameborder='0' framespacing='0' src="<span class='bluetxt'>MyMain.htm</span>" name="<span class='bluetxt'>MyFrameTwo</span>"&gt;&lt;/frame&gt;<br>
		&lt;/frameset&gt;<br>&lt;/html&gt;</td></tr></table>
<h1>Step 2: Inserting necessary codes</h1>
<p><b><font size="4">i) Add the below script in the &lt;BODY&gt; of MyframeOne,
immediately following the tag:</font></b></p>
<table cellSpacing="0" border="0">
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td width="50" rowSpan="4"></td>
      <td>&lt;html&gt;<br>
        &lt;head&gt;your header html&lt;/head&gt;</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>&lt;body&gt;</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="bluewhite">&lt;script type='text/javascript'&gt;<br>
        //HV Menu- by Ger Versluis (http://www.burmees.nl/)<br>
        //Submitted to Dynamic Drive (http://www.dynamicdrive.com)<br>
        //Visit http://www.dynamicdrive.com for this script and more
        <p>function
        Go(){return}&lt;/script&gt;<br>
        &lt;script type='text/javascript'
        src='exmplmenu_var.js'&gt;&lt;/script&gt;<br>
        &lt;script type='text/javascript' src='menu_com.js'&gt;&lt;/script&gt;</p>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>your html<br>
        &lt;/body&gt;<br>
        &lt;/html&gt;</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>
(Where <span class="redtxt">MyFrameOne</span> is the name of the navigation
frame.)
<p><b><font size="4">ii) Then, add the below code inside the &lt;BODY&gt; tag
itself of MyFrameTwo, as follows:</font></b></p>
<table>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td width="50" rowSpan="3"></td>
      <td>&lt;html&gt;<br>
        &lt;head&gt;your header html&lt;/head&gt;</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="bluewhite">&lt;body <b>onload=&quot;javascript:{if(parent.frames[0]&amp;&amp;parent.frames['<span class="redtxt">MyFrameOne</span>'].Go)parent.frames['<span class="redtxt">MyFrameOne</span>'].Go()}</b>&quot;&gt;</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>your html<br>
        &lt;/body&gt;<br>
        &lt;/html&gt;</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>
(Where <span class="redtxt">MyFrameOne</span> is the name of the navigation
frame.)
